# Matex Operational Rules

## Logistics (logistics-mcp)

### Shipment Workflow
1. Order completed → shipping requirements auto-generated from order details
2. Multi-carrier quotes dispatched simultaneously to `carriers-bridge`
3. Buyer/seller selects carrier → BOL auto-generated
4. Carrier dispatches pickup → GPS tracking activated
5. Weight recorded at pickup (W2 — carrier certified scale)
6. Delivery confirmed with photo POD uploaded to `logistics_mcp.shipments`
7. Weight recorded at destination (W3 — buyer scale, if certified)

### Carrier Integration (carriers-bridge)
Integrated carriers: Day & Ross, Manitoulin Transport, Purolator Freight, GoFor Industries, Canada Cartage, Uber Freight/Convoy.
- Always request quotes from ALL integrated carriers simultaneously and rank by price/transit/rating.
- Generate BOL immediately upon booking confirmation.
- CO2 emissions (`co2_emissions_kg`) must be calculated per shipment for ESG reporting.

### Hazmat Rules
- Set `hazmat_class` on every shipment (default `none`).
- Classes 8 (corrosives — lead-acid batteries) and 9 (misc — lithium-ion scrap) are most common.
- Carriers transporting hazmat must have TDG certification recorded in their profile.
- Auto-apply TDGR classification based on material category.

