## Cross-Border Trade

### Supported Corridors
- Canada → US: Ferrous scrap, aluminum, copper, paper (USMCA, ITAR, TSCA)
- US → Canada: Mixed metals, plastics, e-waste (CBSA import rules, CEPA)
- Cross-border triggers a full customs workflow automatically.

### Auto-Generated Documents
- Commercial Invoice (all cross-border)
- Packing List (all cross-border)
- USMCA Certificate of Origin (for duty-free claims)
- Export Declaration B13A via CBSA CERS API (Canada exports > $2,000)
- Hazmat Declaration (TDGR/DOT regulated materials)

### Currency Management
- Transaction currency locked at purchase confirmation (rate guaranteed 24 hours).
- Buyer pays in preferred currency (CAD or USD); conversion fee = 0.5% markup on mid-market.
- Use XE or Open Exchange Rates API for real-time rates — never hardcode conversion factors.
- All financial reports show both original currency AND CAD equivalent for CRA compliance.

### OFAC / CBSA Compliance
- Screen all US-bound transactions against OFAC SDN list.
- Monitor for anti-circumvention: flag transshipment patterns.
- Basel Convention: hazardous waste cannot cross borders without prior informed consent.

