## Environmental Compliance

### Environmental Permit Lifecycle
- Sellers declare material handling activities and upload applicable permits at registration.
- Automated expiry alerts at: 90 days, 60 days, 30 days before permit expiry.
- Expired permit → automatic listing suspension until renewed permit is uploaded.
- Each listing requires environmental classification: `non-hazardous`, `potentially_hazardous`, or `hazardous`.

### Chain of Custody Requirements (by transaction value)
| Value | Required Documentation |
|---|---|
| < $5,000 | Self-declaration of ownership |
| $5,000 – $25,000 | Purchase invoice or generation certificate |
| $25,000 – $100,000 | Source documentation + chain of custody form |
| > $100,000 | Full provenance documentation + mandatory third-party site inspection |

### Theft Prevention
- First-time sellers of high-theft materials (copper, catalytic converters): 72-hour cooling period before listing goes live.
- Pattern detection: flag unusually frequent listings from individual accounts in high-theft categories.
- Geographic anomaly: flag if seller location is inconsistent with material source location.

